<!--[[Image:kevin.welner.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Kevin G. Welner {{PD-author|Kevin G. Welner}} {{deletable image-caption|Friday, October 29, 2010|date=October 2010}}]]-->
'''Kevin G. Welner''' (born 1963) is professor of education at the [[University of Colorado Boulder]] School of Education, where he chairs the Educational Foundations Policy and Practice program area. He co-founded<ref name=Sparks2010>{{cite news|last1=Sparks|first1=Sarah D.|title=Think Tank Critics Launch Policy Center - Education Week|url=https://www.edweek.org/ew/articles/2010/09/29/05thinktank.h30.html|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Education Week|date=29 September 2010|language=en}}</ref> and is Director of the [[National Education Policy Center]]. He has authored or edited 11 books<ref name=worldcat>{{cite web|title=WorldCat Profile for Welner, Kevin Grant 1963-|url=http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-no99091842/|website=WorldCat|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref> and more than 100 articles and book chapters<ref>{{cite web|title=Google Scholar Citations for Kevin Welner|url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=-74qCF0AAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao|website=scholar.google.com}}</ref><ref name=WelnerCV>{{cite web|title=Kevin Welner's Curriculm Vitae at CU Boulder|url=https://www.colorado.edu/education/kevin-welner|website=School of Education|accessdate=17 May 2018|language=en|date=4 September 2013}}</ref> concerning [[education policy|education policy and law]].

==Career==
Welner received his J.D. at [[UCLA School of Law]] and his Ph.D. from [[UCLA Graduate School of Education and Information Studies|UCLA Graduate School of Education & Information Studies]].<ref name=WelnerCV /> During his early career he received a National Academy of Education/Spencer Post-Doctoral Fellowship.<ref>{{cite web|title=2000 NAEd/Spencer Postdoctoral Fellows - National Academy of Education|url=https://naeducation.org/naedspencer-postdoctoral-fellowship-program/2000-naedspencer-postdoctoral-fellows/|website=National Academy of Education|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref> 

In 2005, Welner conducted research on school vouchers as a resident of the [[Rockefeller_Foundation#Bellagio_Center|Rockefeller Foundation Bellagio Center]].<ref name=WelnerCV /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Welner|first1=Kevin|title=Tax credits, school choice and 'neovouchers': What you need to know|url=https://theconversation.com/tax-credits-school-choice-and-neovouchers-what-you-need-to-know-74808|accessdate=24 May 2018|work=The Conversation|ref=See this article's "disclosure statement"|language=en}}</ref> That research was later published as a major work on school vouchers, ''NeoVouchers: The Emergence of Tuition Tax Credits for Private Schooling.'' The book provided an early explanation of the legal and policy issues surrounding a then-new type of private school vouchers. These neo-vouchers were created by giving large tax credits for donations to organizations that then packaged those donations as vouchers to fund tuition.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Schaeffer|first1=Adam B.|title=Book Review: NeoVouchers: The Emergence of Tuition Tax Credits for Private Schooling|journal=Journal of School Choice|date=19 June 2009|volume=3|issue=2|pages=200–202|doi=10.1080/15582150902987566}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Anomaly|first1=Jonny|title=Book Review: Neovouchers: The Emergence of Tuition Tax Credits for Private Schooling.|journal=Education Review|date=17 May 2011|volume=14|url=http://www.edrev.info/reviews/rev1087.pdf|accessdate=22 May 2018}}</ref> 

In 2012, Welner was inducted as an American Educational Research Association Fellow, a recognition of his substantial contributions to the field of education research.<ref>{{cite web|title=AERA Fellows|url=http://www.aera.net/About-AERA/Fellows|website=www.aera.net}}</ref> These contributions include studies into the public right to education, [[Tracking (education)|tracking]], [[school vouchers]], [[school choice]], [[educational equity|educational equity,]] and the use of research.<ref name=WelnerCV /><ref>{{cite web|title=Source Profile for Kevin Welner - Education Writers Association|url=https://www.ewa.org/source/kevin-welner|website=Education Writers Association|language=en}}</ref> Welner is also notable for making technical research documents that are accessible to the general public,<ref>{{cite news|last1=McSpadden|first1=Kay|title=We must attack opportunity gaps at their root causes|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/opinion/op-ed/article68292712.html|accessdate=24 May 2018|work=charlotteobserver|language=en}}</ref> and for participating in public academic debates on education reform issues such as standardized testing,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Levesque|first1=Patricia|last2=Welner|first2=Kevin|title=Is Testing Students the Answer to America's Education Woes?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2015/05/04/is-testing-students-the-answer-to-americas-education-woes|accessdate=17 May 2018|work=The New York Times|date=4 May 2015|language=en}}</ref> school choice,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hobson|first1=Jeremy|title=A Closer Look At The Debate Over Charter Schools|url=http://www.wbur.org/hereandnow/2016/10/13/charter-schools-harm-good|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=www.wbur.org|date=13 October 2016|language=en}}</ref> and school vouchers. 

Welner joined the faculty of the University of Colorado Boulder School of Education {{when|date=May 2018}} where he serves as a professor of educational foundation policy and practice.<ref name=WelnerCV />

